RESID:AA0114]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it represents a molecular function.\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28482\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\n\n\n---TERM-END---\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0018237\nname: urease activator activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Increases the activity of urease by promoting the incorporation of nickel into the active site.\" [GOC:mah, PMID:16244137]\nsynonym: \"urease activase activity\" EXACT []\nintersection_of: GO:0140677 ! molecular function activator activity\nintersection_of: directly_positively_regulates GO:0009039 ! urease activity\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0018238\nname: obsolete peptidyl-lysine carboxyethylation\nnamespace: biological_process\nalt_id: GO:0018239\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. The modification of peptidyl-lysine to form peptidyl-N6-1-carboxyethyl-L-lysine.\" [RESID:AA0115]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it represents a molecular function.\nsynonym: \"protein amino acid carboxyethylation\" EXACT []\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28482\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\n\n\n---TERM-END---\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0018240\nname: obsolete protein S-linked glycosylation via cysteine\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. The glycosylation of protein via the sulfur atom of peptidyl-cysteine, forming S-glycosyl-L-cysteine.\" [RESID:AA0152]\ncomment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term represents a molecular function.\nsynonym: \"protein amino acid S-linked glycosylation via cysteine\" EXACT [GOC:bf]\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-announcements/issues/988\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: GO:0018280\n\n\n---TERM-END---\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0018241\nname: obsolete protein O-linked glycosylation via hydroxylysine\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. The glycosylation of protein via the O5 atom of peptidyl-hydroxylysine, forming O